Bring the Future of Media and Entertainment into Focus

The State of the Art Redefined

The film and television industries are constantly innovating and reinventing their production pipelines to address the growing demand for high-quality content while maintaining tight timelines in a globally distributed workforce. In addition, streaming services are creating the need for constant releases and refreshes to satisfy an increasing subscriber base. As a result, studios are now turning to AI, virtual production, real-time rendering, and content collaboration to dramatically accelerate production—from desktop to data center to cloud.

NVIDIA Solutions For M&E
Request a Consultation

Explore What’s Next in AI, Accelerated Computing, and Beyond With the Best of GTC

Developer Conference March 20-23 | Keynote March 21

Catch these recommended sessions on-demand.

Advances in Data-Parallel Production Rendering at Scale

We'll describe some of the latest advancements we're making for data-parallel production rendering on modern hardware such as GPUs and CPUs. Topics will include improved parallelism in OpenSubdiv, production rendering performance improvements, improved parallelization overall, and some details related our texture cache implementation and the Lama production shaders.

View Session

Emerging Tech in Animation Pre-Production

At Sony Pictures Animation, we're always looking for ways to improve the creative pre-production and storytelling process. We'll explore some of the most recent emerging technologies, such as AI and Omniverse, and how they could impact our workflows.

View Session

Accelerate the Virtual Production Pipeline to Produce an Award-Winning Sci-Fi Short Film

With NVIDIA Omniverse and NVIDIA RTX technology, artists from Versatile Media were able to accelerate their virtual production pipeline and produce a sci-fi short film, "New Air," entirely in an LED volume in only four days using three physical props, with real-time compositing and no visual effects (VFX) added in post-production.

Accelerating Film and TV Production Workflows

Image courtesy of Lucasfilm.

Virtual Production

With the move to shooting visual effects in-camera on virtual production stages, remote virtual art departments can collaborate directly with the set using NVIDIA Omniverse™ Enterprise and their favorite content creation tools like Unreal, Maya, and 3ds Max. Making directorial edits in real time is crucial to keeping costs under control.

Digital Domain

Rendering

Create the most beautiful and accurately lit renders in real-time with NVIDIA RTX™, featuring dedicated RT Cores for ray tracing and Tensor cores for AI denoising, super-sampling, and much more. GPU-accelerated rendering is now available with every major renderer, including Autodesk Arnold, Chaos V-Ray, Maxon Redshift, Isotropix Clarisse, DreamWorks MoonRay, Pixar RenderMan XPU, and NVIDIA Omniverse RTX Renderer.

Artificial Intelligence

AI-enabled features are now available in all of the major content creation applications. Use these AI assistants to reduce repetitive tasks and create content in a fraction of the time. Advanced AI-enabled analytics can help you understand your audience better than ever. The possibilities have become limitless for AI-enhanced content creation, distribution, and monetization.

Solutions for Film and TV

NVIDIA Omniverse

Revolutionize your studio’s production pipeline. NVIDIA Omniverse is an open platform built to accelerate creative production. With one-click interoperability between leading content creation tools and seamless collaboration in an interactive, simulated world, teams are empowered to create at the speed of imagination.

Learn More About Omniverse

RTX Professional Solutions

The industry's most critically acclaimed feature films require the latest technological advancements – from mobile and desktop, to data center and cloud. NVIDIA RTX professional solutions work behind the scenes to give you the precision and power to tell remarkable stories.

Learn More About RTX-Powered Solutions

Studio in the Cloud

As studios become increasingly remote, RTX Virtual Workstation (vWS) enables artists to access powerful virtual workstations from anywhere, while enjoying performance on the same level as physical workstations.

Learn More About RTX vWS

Accelerating Advertising Workflows

Video Production

Edit and color grade in real time without pre-caching or generating proxies. Immerse your audiences with amazing 360-degree video with GPU-accelerated applications like Blackmagic Design DaVinci Resolve and Adobe Premiere Pro.

Multi-Channel Delivery

Deliver 3D graphics and video to any device dynamically using AI. With NVIDIA CloudXR™, smartphones, tablets, and augmented and virtual reality, headsets become windows to completely new worlds.

Artificial Intelligence

Create content faster with AI-accelerated applications like DaVinci Resolve, Autodesk Flame, and Adobe Creative Cloud. Reduce time to insights and sell through ad inventories faster with precise content targeting using deep learning.
